Step 1: Install Yarn
npm install --global yarn

Step 2: Create New Nuxt 2 Project
yarn create nuxt-app <your-project-name>

Step 3: Choose Your Configuration
During the setup process, youâ€™ll be prompted to choose various options for your Nuxt application, such as:

Package manager: Choose Yarn.
UI framework: Select any UI framework you prefer (like Vuetify, Tailwind CSS, etc.).
Server framework: Choose between options like Express, Fastify, etc.
Linting tools: Pick your preferred linting options.
Testing framework: Select if you want to include testing tools.

Step 4: Install Dependencies
yarn install

Step 5: Run Application
yarn dev

Step 6: Build and Start Production
yarn build
yarn start